  "translations": {
    "en": "And the right of your two legs is that you walk not with them toward that which is unlawful for you. You will stand upon the Path with them, so see to it that they do not slip and cause you to fall into the Fire. And the right of your stomach is that you make it not into a container for the forbidden, and you eat no more than your fill. And the right of your private part is that you protect it from fornication, and guard it against being looked upon.",
